SUMMARY:Ann Patchett at Meredith College's Jones Chapel
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ann-patchett-at-meredith-college
 s-jones-chapel-tickets-60627930773\n\nAN ARTS & LECTURE SERIES EVENT:\nA
 nn Patchett joins Quail Ridge Books at Meredith College's Jones Chapel t
 o discuss her new novel\,The Dutch House.\nPlease note that many of thes
 e tickets have already been taken by subscribers to our Arts & Lecture S
 eries\, so availability is extremely limited. \nAnn Patchett\, theNew Yo
 rk Timesbestselling author ofCommonwealthandState of Wonder\, returns wi
 th her most powerful novel to date: a richly moving story that explores 
 the indelible bond between two siblings\, the house of their childhood\,
  and a past that will not let them go.\n'Do you think its possible to ev
 er see the past as it actually was? I asked my sister. We were sitting i
 n her car\, parked in front of the Dutch House in the broad daylight of 
 early summer.\nAt the end of the Second World War\, Cyril Conroy combine
 s luck and a single canny investment to begin an enormous real estate em
 pire\, propelling his family from poverty to enormous wealth. His first 
 order of business is to buy the Dutch House\, a lavish estate in the sub
 urbs outside of Philadelphia. Meant as a surprise for his wife\, the hou
 se sets in motion the undoing of everyone he loves.\nThe story is told b
 y Cyrils son Danny\, as he and his older sister\, the brilliantly acerbi
 c and self-assured Maeve\, are exiled from the house where they grew up 
 by their stepmother. The two wealthy siblings are thrown back into the p
 overty their parents had escaped from and find that all they have to cou
 nt on is one another. It is this unshakeable bond between them that both
  saves their lives and thwarts their futures.\nSet over the course of fi
 ve decades\,The Dutch Houseis a dark fairy tale about two smart people w
 ho cannot overcome their past. Despite every outward sign of success\, D
 anny and Maeve are only truly comfortable when theyre together. Througho
 ut their lives they return to the well-worn story of what theyve lost wi
 th humor and rage. But when at last theyre forced to confront the people
  who left them behind\, the relationship between an indulged brother and
  his ever-protective sister is finally tested.\nThe Dutch Houseis the st
 ory of a paradise lost\, a tour de force that digs deeply into questions
  of inheritance\, love and forgiveness\, of how we want to see ourselves
  and of who we really are. Filled with suspense\, you may read it quickl
 y to find out what happens\, but what happens to Danny and Maeve will st
 ay with you for a very long time.\nEntry fee includes a copy ofThe Dutch
  Houseand one reserved seat. Purchase of the book is required for entran
 ce.\nWe can't wait to see you there!\nFAQs:\nDo I need to buy a ticket t
 o attend?\nEvery attendee needs a ticket. Each ticket includes a copy of
 The Dutch Houseand a reserved seat.\nWhere do I pick up my book(s)/ticke
 t(s)?\nBooks will be available for pickup at Quail Ridge Books through O
 ctober 26th\, and at Will Call in the Jones Chapel on October 27th.\nWil
 l Ann sign books at the event?\nYes.\nPlease note signing line details a
 re subject to change.\nMay I take photos?\nRecording or livestreaming of
  Anns presentation is not allowed. You may take candid photos or livestr
 eam during the singing line. However\, because of the crowd size and tim
 e constraints\, there will beno posedphotos. If you'd like to take a pic
 ture with Karen while she is signing your book\, a QRB bookseller will b
 e on hand to take the photo with your camera or phone.\nHow is the signi
 ng line organized?\nPresentation seats are general admission. Your signi
 ng line ticket has a letter on it. Letters are issued in the order in wh
 ich your ticket was purchased\, so it is to your advantage to order earl
 y. When we call your letter\, you will line up to meet Ann.\nWhen should
  I get there?\nWill Call details to come.\nHow do I get there?\nFor GPS 
 or mapping apps use:\n3800 Hillsborough StreetRaleigh\, North Carolina 2
 7609\nWhat's the refund policy?\nYou may request a refund through Eventb
 rite up to7days prior to the event.\nIs it okay if the name on my ticket
  or registration doesn't match the person who attends?\nAs long as each 
 member of your party has a ticket with a valid QR code\, the names do no
 t need to match.At Will Call just ask for the name of the ticket buyer.\
 nWe encourage you to purchase your tickets early for early placement in 
 the signing line. However\, please note that event details are subject t
 o change. Please check back closer to the event date and watch your emai
 l for any updates.\n\n
CREATED:20260313T024209Z
GEO:35.7944904;-78.68789709999999
LOCATION:Jones Chapel\, 3800 Hillsborough St.\, Raleigh\, NC 27607
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ann-patchett-at-meredith-colleges-jones-
 chapel-tickets-60627930773
LAST-MODIFIED:20190822T025356Z
UID:60627930773
END:VEVENT
