SUMMARY:Shannon Messenger in-conversation with Kwame Mbalia
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/shannon-messenger-in-conversatio
 n-with-kwame-mbalia-tickets-69015237433\n\nThe event is currently sold o
 ut. To join the waitlist\, click the TICKETS button and follow the promp
 ts. To hear about future events\, please join our email newsletterhere.\
 nQuail Ridge Books and Meredith College Friends of the Library are proud
  to host Shannon Messenger\, author of the New York Times bestselling se
 ries: Keeper of the Lost Cities. Shannon will be presenting and signing 
 the eighth book in her series\, Legacy\, at the Meredith College Jones C
 hapel on Thursday\, November 21st\, 2019 @ 6:00 p.m. She will be in-conv
 ersation with Kwame Mbalia\, author of Tristan Strong Punches a Hole in 
 the Sky. Get your tickets now!\nBelow are some Frequently Asked Question
 s:\nDo I need to buy a ticket to attend the event with my child?\nEvery 
 attendee needs a ticket. Each GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET qualifies for ONE
  free PARENT COMPANION TICKET. Each free PARENT COMPANION TICKET must co
 rrespond to ONE distinct GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET. PARENT COMPANION TICK
 ETS must correspond to GENERAL ADMISSION TICKETS in a 1:1 ratio. If two 
 or more people would like to accompanying the child\, they must purchase
  a second GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET\, to be eligible to receive a second 
 COMPANION TICKET. All GENERAL ADMISSION TICKETS include a copy of Keeper
  of the Lost Cities: Legacy.\nTicket Types:\nGENERAL ADMISSION TICKET / 
 $24.11\nIncludes a copy of Keeper of the Lost Cities: Legacy\, a present
 ation ticket\, and a signing line ticket. This is a required ticket - al
 l groups must include at least one GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET per each PAR
 ENT COMPANION TICKET.\nPARENT COMPANION TICKET / $0\nIncludes entry to t
 he presentation and the signing line. This ticket is for adults accompan
 ying children holding GENERAL ADMISSION TICKETS. EACH PARENT COMPANION T
 ICKET must correspond to ONE GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET to be valid. Compa
 nion tickets must correspond to GENERAL ADMISSION tickets in a 1:1 ratio
 . If two adults would like to accompanying the child\, they must purchas
 e a second GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET\, to be eligible to receive a second
  COMPANION TICKET.\nWhere do I pick up my book(s)/ticket(s)?\nShannon wi
 ll presign all copies of Legacy. You may join the signing line after the
  presenation to have Legacy personalized.  **You can pick up your book a
 nd signing line ticket on the day of the event at Will Call. Unfortunate
 ly\, you will not be able to pick up your book/ticket(s) prior to the ev
 ent.**\nWill Shannon sign books at the event?\nYes. Your ticket(s) inclu
 de a signing line ticket. Shannon will personalize and sign copies of LE
 GACY that were included with the event tickets. Her other titles will be
  signed and available for purchase at the event. She will sign ONE (1)  
 additional backlist title brought from home per GENERAL ADMISSION ticket
 . Due to the large crowd size\, Shannon will only sign books\, no fan ar
 t\, shirts\, etc.\nPlease note signing line details are subject to chang
 e.\nWill Kwame Mbalia also be signing books at the event? \nKwame Mbalia
  will also be available to sign and personalize his book at the event. \
 nHow can I buy Kwame Mbalia's book?\nCopies will be available for sale a
 t the event. You are also welcome to pre-order the book here. \nMay I ta
 ke photos?\nRecording or livestreaming of Shannons presentation is not a
 llowed. You may take candid photos or livestream during the signing line
 . However\, because of the crowd size and time constraints\, there will 
 be no posed photos. If you'd like to take a picture with Shannon while s
 he is signing your book\, a QRB bookseller will be on hand to take the p
 hoto with your camera or phone. \nHow is the signing line organized?\nPr
 esentation seats are general admission. Your signing line ticket has a l
 etter on it. Letters are issued in the order in which your ticket was pu
 rchased\, so it is to your advantage to order early. When we call your l
 etter\, you will line up to meet Shannon.\nWhen should I get there?\nWil
 l Call details to come.\nHow do I get there?\nFor GPS or mapping apps us
 e:\n3800 Hillsborough StreetRaleigh\, North Carolina 27609\nWhat's the r
 efund policy?\nYou may request a refund through Eventbrite up to 7 days 
 prior to the event. \nIs it okay if the name on my ticket or registratio
 n doesn't match the person who attends?\nWe understand that sometimes sc
 hedules change and another adult may end up accompanying your child to y
 our event. As long as each member of your party has a ticket with a vali
 d QR code\, the names do not need to match. At Will Call just ask for th
 e name of the ticket buyer.\nWe encourage you to purchase your tickets e
 arly for early placement in the signing line. However\, please note that
  event details are subject to change. Please check back closer to the ev
 ent date and watch your email for any updates.\n\n
CREATED:20260313T024209Z
GEO:35.7944904;-78.68789709999999
LOCATION:Meredith College Jones Chapel\, 3800 Hillsborough Street \, Rale
 igh\,  North Carolina 27609
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/shannon-messenger-in-conversation-with-k
 wame-mbalia-tickets-69015237433
