SUMMARY:Randall Munroe at NC State University's Hunt Library
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/randall-munroe-at-nc-state-unive
 rsitys-hunt-library-tickets-61709845810\n\nQuail Ridge Books is delighte
 d to announce that Randall Munroe will discuss his new book\, How To: Ab
 surd Scientific Advice for Common Real-World Problems at NC State Univer
 sity's Hunt Library on Thursday\, September 19 at 7 pm.\nFrom the brilli
 ant mind behind the wildly popular webcomic XKCD and the #1 New York Tim
 es bestsellers What If? and Thing Explainer comes the world's most enter
 taining and useless self-help guide.\nRandall will be in conversation wi
 th Katie Mack\, (a.k.a. Dr Katherine J Mack) astrophysicist/cosmologist\
 , occasional freelance science writer\, connoisseur of cosmic catastroph
 es and Assistant Professor of Physics at North Carolina State University
 . Her book\, The End of Everything\, will be out next year.\nEach ticket
  includes a copy of How To: Absurd Scientific Advice for Common Real-Wor
 ld Problems\, a reserved seat\, a place in the signing line\, and ticket
  fees. \nFor students: There are a limited number of free tickets availa
 ble for current NC State University students on a first-come\, first-ser
 ved basis\, one ticket per student. To reserve your free ticket\, sign u
 p atthis link. Please note: free student tickets do not include a copy o
 f the book\; however\, books will be available for purchase on-site. \nT
 his event is co-sponsored by NC State University Libraries.\nWe can't wa
 it to see you there!\nFAQs\nDo I need to buy a book to attend the event?
  \nYes. \nEach ticket gets you a reserved (not assigned) seat and a book
 .\nWhat if the event is sold out? \nWe encourage you to join the waitlis
 t. If a ticket opens up you will have the option of buying it then.\nHow
  can I buy additional copies of Mr. Munroe's books?\nYou can buy additio
 nal copies of his books at the event\, while supplies last. \nWhere do I
  pick up my book/ticket?\nYou may pick up your book and ticket at Quail 
 Ridge Books from September 3rd through September 18th or you may wait an
 d pick them up at the Hunt Library on September 19th\, starting at 5:30 
 p.m. \nWhen should I get there?\nWill Call will open at 5:30 p.m.\, and 
 doors to the auditorium will open at 6:30 p.m. We suggest arriving by 6:
 15 p.m. to allow time for parking and book/ticket pickup. \nCan I take p
 hotos?\nYes.\nHow are the reserved seats assigned?\nEach ticket will hav
 e a guaranteed seat\; however\, seats are not assigned and will be avail
 able on a first-come\, first-serve basis. Please note\, tickets may sell
  quickly\, and it is to your advantage to purchase early.\nHow do I get 
 there?\nFor GPS or mapping apps use:\nThe James B. Hunt Jr. Library\n107
 0 Partners Way\nRaleigh NC 27606\nWhere can I park?\nParking is free and
  open to the public after 5:00 p.m. on weekdays. \nServices \nAll restro
 oms doors are painted yellow. There are restrooms located on the first a
 nd second floors. For food and snack\, check out Common Grounds Cafe on 
 the first floor of the library.\nWhat's the refund policy?\nAttendees ca
 n receive refunds up to 7 days before the event date through Eventbrite.
  If you miss the refund window and are unable to make it to the event\, 
 you can pick up your signed copy of How To: Absurd Scientific Advice for
  Common Real-World Problems at Quail Ridge Books on or after Friday\, Se
 ptember 20th.\nDo I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?\nQuail
  Ridge Books will have a list of attendees at Will Call. There's no need
  to print your EventBrite ticket.
CREATED:20260313T024209Z
GEO:35.7692923;-78.67663820000001
