SUMMARY:Two-time Newbery Medalist and Best-Selling Author Kate DiCamillo 
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/two-time-newbery-medalist-and-be
 st-selling-author-kate-dicamillo-tickets-62356237184\n\nThe event is cur
 rently sold out\, and our waitlist is full. To hear about future events\
 , please join our email newsletterhere.\nQuail Ridge Books and NC State 
 Friends of the Libary are proud to present two-time Newbery Medalist and
  #1 New York Times' Bestselling Author Kate DiCamillo. Kate will be pres
 enting and signing her new book Beverly\, Right Here at the Hunt Library
  on Saturday\, January 11\, 2020 @ 2:00 p.m. Get your tickets now!\nBelo
 w are some Frequently Asked Questions:\nDo I need to buy a ticket to att
 end the event with my child?\nYes. All adults need to purchase a ticket.
  CHILD COMPANION TICKETS (age 14 & under) tickets are free for this even
 t\, if each child is accompanied by a ticket-holding adult. Tickets shou
 ld be selected in cart at time of purchase. Each free CHILD COMPANION TI
 CKET must correspond to ONE distinct GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET. CHILD COM
 PANION TICKETS must correspond to GENERAL ADMISSION TICKETS in a 1:1 rat
 io. If a parent would like two children to attend with them\, they must 
 purchase a second GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET to be eligible to receive a s
 econd CHILD COMPANION TICKET. All GENERAL ADMISSION TICKETS include a co
 py of Beverly\, Right Here.\nTicket Types:\nGENERAL ADMISSION TICKET / $
 18.99 \nIncludes a copy of Beverly\, Right Here\, a presentation ticket\
 , and a signing line ticket. This is a required ticket - all groups must
  include at least one GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET per each CHILD COMPANION 
 TICKET.\nCHILD COMPANION TICKET / $0 \nIncludes entry to the presentatio
 n and the signing line. This ticket is for children14 and under only. EA
 CH CHILD COMPANION TICKET must correspond to ONE GENERAL ADMISSION TICKE
 T to be valid. Child tickets must correspond to GENERAL ADMISSION ticket
 s in a 1:1 ratio. If a parent would like two children to attend with the
 m\, they must purchase a second GENERAL ADMISSION TICKET\, to be eligibl
 e to receive a second CHILD COMPANION TICKET. \nWhere do I pick up my bo
 ok(s)/ticket(s)?\nThe book is published on Tuesday\, September 24th\, 20
 19. You may pick up your book\, and signing line ticket\, at Quail Ridge
  Books on or after September 24th. You may also choose to pick up your b
 ook and signing line ticket on the day of the event at Will Call on the 
 main floor lobby of the Hunt Library. Will Call will open at 1:00 p.m. o
 n Saturday\, January 11th.\nWill Kate sign books at the event? \nYes. Yo
 ur ticket(s) include a signing line ticket. Please note that signing det
 ails are subject to change. Please check back in January for the most up
 -to-date details.\nMay I take photos? \nYou may take candid photos durin
 g the singing line. However\, because of the crowd size and time constra
 ints\, there will be no posed photos. If you'd like to take a picture wi
 th Kate while she is signing your book\, a QRB bookseller will be on han
 d to take the photo with your camera or phone. \nHow is the signing line
  organized?\nPresentation seats are general admission. Your signing line
  ticket has a letter on it. Letters are issued in the order in which you
 r ticket was purchased\, so it is to your advantage to order early. When
  we call your letter\, you will line up to meet Kate. \nWhen should I ge
 t there?\nPresentation doors open at 1:00 pm. Seating is general admissi
 on. Will Call will open no later than 1:00 pm. If you do not pick up you
 r book at Quail Ridge books prior to the day of the event\, we suggest y
 ou arrive with enough time to be at Will Call at 1:00 pm.\nHow do I get 
 there?\nFor GPS or mapping apps use:\n1070 Partners Way\nRaleigh\, NC 27
 606\nFrom RDU Airport and Points West\nTake Aviation Parkway to I-40 eas
 t. Take I-40 to I-440 South-Outer Beltline. Take I-440 to Exit 2\, Weste
 rn Boulevard (towards downtown Raleigh). Straight on Western\; turn righ
 t on Avent Ferry Road. Turn left on Varsity Drive (entrance to Centennia
 l Campus). Where Varsity Drive ends\, turn right onto Partners Way. The 
 James B Hunt Jr. Library is on the left near the end of Partners Way.\nW
 here should I park?\nThe public pay lots are free on Saturdays. For a pa
 rking map click here.\nServices \nAll restrooms doors are painted yellow
 . There are restrooms located on the first and second floors. For food a
 nd snack\, check out Common Grounds Cafe on the first floor of the libra
 ry.\nWhat's the refund policy?\nYou may request a refund through Eventbr
 ite up to 30 days prior to the event. However\, because your ticket incl
 udes a copy of Beverly\, Right Here\, Quail Ridge will not issue any ref
 unds after the book has been picked up from Quail Ridge Books by the tic
 ket holder. \nIs it ok if the name on my ticket or registration doesn't 
 match the person who attends?\nWe understand that sometimes schedules ch
 ange and another parent may end up accompanying your child to your event
 . As long as each member of your party has a ticket with a valid QR code
 \, the names do not need to match. However the free CHILD COMPANION tick
 et can only be used by a child 14 or under.\nWe encourage you to purchas
 e your tickets early for early placement in the signing line. However\, 
 please note that due to the long lead time for this event\, event detail
 s are subject to change. Please check back closer to the event date and 
 watch your email for any updates.
CREATED:20260313T024209Z
GEO:35.7692923;-78.67663820000001
LOCATION:James B. Hunt Jr. Library\, 1070 Partners Way\, Raleigh\, NC 276
 06
