SUMMARY:Louise Penny
DESCRIPTION:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/louise-penny-tickets-60954726227
 \n\n Quail Ridge Books is thrilled to announce that Louise Penny will di
 scuss her Three Pines mysteries featuring Armand Gamache at the NCSU McK
 immon Center on Wednesday\, June 26 at 7 pm. This event is presented wit
 h support from the NC State University Libraries.\nEach ticket includes 
 either a copy of the paperback or hardcover of KINGDOM OF THE BLIND\; or
  a pre-order of her new hardcover\, A BETTER MAN. Kingdom of the Blind g
 oes on sale in paperback on June 25th and the paperback or hardcover may
  be picked up at the event. A BETTER MAN goes on sale August 27th and pr
 e-ordered copies may be picked up at Quail Ridge Books on or after Augus
 t 27. All three options include a book\, a reserved seat\, and ticket fe
 es. Purchase of one of the books is required for entrance.\nWe can't wai
 t to see you there!\nFAQs\nDo I need to buy a book to attend the event? 
 \nYes. \nEach ticket gets you a reserved (not assigned) seat and a book.
 \nTicket Options:\nThe only difference between the ticket options listed
  above is the book included with the ticket. You may choose to get a pap
 erback or hardcover copy of Kingdom of the Blind\, or to pre-order the n
 ewest Three Pines mystery coming in August\, A Better Man.\nWhat if the 
 ticket option (book) I want is sold out? \nDue to popularity\, one optio
 n may sell out quickly. If there are other tickets available\, please se
 lect another title\, then email us through Eventbrite and let us know yo
 ur preferred title.\nHow can I buy additional copies of Ms. Penny's book
 s?\nYou can buy additional signed copies of her books at the event. \nWh
 ere do I pick up my book/ticket?\nYour ticket (and pre-signed book if yo
 u are ordering Kingdom of the Blind) will be available at the event at t
 he McKimmon Center. You may pick up your ticket as early as 5:30 p.m on 
 Wednesday\, June 26th. \nWhen should I get there?\nWill Call will open a
 t 5:30 p.m. and doors to the auditorium will open at 6:30 p.m. We sugges
 t arriving by 6:15 to allow time for parking and book/ticket pickup. \nW
 ill Louise Penny sign books at the event?\nAll copies of Kingdom of the 
 Blind will be pre-signed. Ms. Penny will not be signing at the event. \n
 Can I take photos?\nYou may take candid photos during the presentation. 
 However\, because of the crowd size and time constraints\, there will be
  no posed photos. \nHow are the reserved seats assigned?\nEach ticket wi
 ll have a seat\; however\, seats are not assigned and will be available 
 on a first-come\, first-serve basis. Please note\, tickets may sell quic
 kly and it is to your advantage to purchase early.\nHow do I get there?\
 nFor GPS or mapping apps use:\nMcKimmon Center\n1101 Gorman Street\nRale
 igh NC 27606\nWhere can I park?\nParking in the front lots of the McKimm
 on Center is free and usually plentiful. There are three smaller parking
  lots on each side of the Center that are reserved for University employ
 ees. Visitors are asked to park in designated visitor parking spaces in 
 order to avoid ticketing. \nWhat's the refund policy?\nAttendees can rec
 eive refunds up to 7 days before the event date through Eventbrite. If y
 ou miss the refund window\, and are unable to make it to the event\, you
  can pick up your signed Kingdom of the Blind paperback at Quail Ridge B
 ooks on or after Thursday\, June 27th or hardcover A Better Man on or af
 ter Tuesday\, August 27th. \nDo I have to bring my printed ticket to the
  event?\nYou can bring your printed ticket\, or you can show us your tic
 ket (with QR code) on your phone. You must show the ticket to pick up yo
 ur ticket and/or book.\n\n
